The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses deep exploration, which is a challenge in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a variation of DQN, which is a popular algorithm in robotics (cs.RO).
